author: @PatrickBateman12420
text: I shelled out $750 (at a discount) for the exam prep course. The course offers a mockup exam which is extremely valuable. Using Associate Cert. preparation is NOT enough. For example, an exam question requires us to know the difference between Rank Dense vs. Unique, Initial SQL vs. Custom SQL ... the title sounds cool, but the exam is challenging if you haven't used Tableau Desktop/Prep/Server for a while (I would say years). Long term, I think the same is going to be a requirement. Short term, probably not ... I took the exam on March 4, 2022, and was still one of the first 1,000 (got this early bird thing) which tells me the demand is still low (or many fail?).
